There is no accurate data on how many pregnant women are in Wuhan, but their lives have been completely disrupted by the epidemic.

The full text is 3588 words and takes about 7 minutes to read

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
February 1, in Wuhan, a new type of pneumonia in a designated hospital for special patients on the second day, Gong Lin gave birth to a 7.1 Jin baby boy, mother and son in good condition. Photo courtesy of the respondents

HSINKING, Xie Lei, editor, Joe Yifei, proofread by Jay Hu, Xu Li Yang

Perhaps, grow up, this 7.1 Jin baby boy is hard to understand, 2020 when he came to the world has many twists and turns.

On February 1, his mother gave birth in Wuhan, Hubei Province. Earlier, his grandmother and his father have confirmed the infection of new pneumonia. After being admitted, my mother was also diagnosed with new pneumonia.

The two-day-old baby boy is currently under normal care in a separate nursery while his mother, Gong Lin, is being treated in isolation in hospital.

Under the pneumonia epidemic in Wuhan, such as Gong Lin maternal fertility problems once plagued many families... they face what kind of difficulties? How has the epidemic changed their lives?

━━━━━

One of the beds felt like winning the five million lottery

Gong and her husband, Zhang Li, moved to Wuhan last year. In May 2019, Gong was pregnant with her second child. With the baby on the way, the whole family is looking forward to the birth.

Before the pneumonia epidemic, the couple rarely went out. On the second day of the Lunar New Year, the husband first began to respond, first was nasal congestion, cough, took the temperature, 37.1 °c, then let the whole family take the temperature, the mother-in-law's temperature has reached 38.1 °c, it was discovered that it may be a new type of pneumonia.

After her husband and her mother-in-law were separated for three days, Gong, who was 38 weeks + 3, also began to develop symptoms such as nasal congestion, diarrhea, chills and fever.

"There are already two new-type virus infections in the house, I should also be infected. " Gong Lin had a bad feeling.

Seeing that his wife, who was about to give birth, might also have contracted pneumonia, Zhang Li spent the day on the phone, contacting several designated hospitals in Wuhan, where he was advised not to come if he had mild symptoms. According to documents released by the Wuhan Prevention and Control Headquarters, there are four hospitals that can accept pregnant women, two of which are in Caidian District, far from their homes. Traffic in Wuhan is stagnant, they don't have a car at home, and they contact the community. The community report said that for safety reasons, the community can not send a car to pick up and send fever patients, can only report, waiting arrangements.

After making numerous calls for help, an ambulance was called with the help of the Gutian district staff and they were taken to the back Lake area of Wuhan Central Hospital. But after Lake Hospital area also did not have a bed at that time, the delivery room is still under reconstruction, can not receive pregnant women. And the hospital can only do blood and CT, can not do the nucleic acid reagent test.

"The general outpatient service does not receive the fever pregnant woman, the fever outpatient service can only do the blood routine, can not judge whether is infected, takes the CT to the pregnant woman not to be safe, also does not have the nucleic acid reagent to be possible to use. All the government-appointed hospitals, all the phone calls, no pregnant women. Trapped in an "endless loop, " Zhang Li said.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On the night of January 30, Gong Lin sat at the door of a designated hospital, waiting for her husband to find his car.

While Gong's family was struggling, Liu's family was seeking medical help. Due on February 12, she was diagnosed with new pneumonia on January 27.

The doctor suggested that the problem must be solved as soon as possible, otherwise it will have a great impact on the fetal heartbeat. Liu yuting family call 120 to the province maternal and child health care hospital ambulance, sent to the hospital, was told that infected pregnant women can not be admitted. They contacted each of the four designated hospitals on the government's list, and the waiting list was as grim as ever -- no beds or protective equipment was in short supply.

"having a bed is like winning the five million lottery, " said Liu's sister

"during the special period of the epidemic, we know that all the units are also overworked. But we especially hope to be able to give a special group, such as pregnant women with fever, a special channel to see a doctor, " Gong told the Beijing News.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Detection of nucleic acid reagent in Puerpera Liu yu-ting. Photo courtesy of the respondents

Volunteer organizations are on the move

Volunteer Dolphin, the head of a children's charity, joined the Volunteer Group on Jan. 23 after she realized that the pregnant and lying-in women in Wuhan needed help. On the same day, many pregnant women in Wuhan asked for help: The hospital is crowded, for fear of cross-infection; fixed-point hospital beds are tight, unable to receive pregnant women; "closed city" caused traffic inconvenience, can not find a car to take to the hospital when Labor..

On Jan. 26, the dolphins and their colleagues set up a wechat group called "left-behind pregnant women in Wuhan. " Soon, more than 200 pregnant women from Wuhan joined the group, and about a quarter of them will give birth within a month. Due to travel inconvenience and face a variety of practical problems, the "mother-to-be" put the hope on the volunteers.

Dolphins, through the network and other channels to help docking needs of pregnant and lying-in women, volunteers will first screening classification, according to the expected date of delivery, whether fever, confirmed infection, and other circumstances, to provide corresponding help to pregnant and lying-in women.

In large groups, pregnant and lying-in women can chat with each other and exchange experiences. If they have any questions, they can ask the professional doctors in the group to answer them. For Women who are close to their due date or are already at high risk, the volunteer team will form small groups and arrange for professional obstetricians and gynaecologists, nurses to provide guidance, as well as social workers to provide psychological support and emotional support.

The team will learn about the symptoms of the woman, the results of the tests and whether to test for nucleic acids, the dolphins said. If need to see a doctor, will help contact the community, hospitals and so on, in advance to determine whether pregnant and lying-in women can go for testing, can be admitted to treatment. Since pregnant women and their families don't have the energy to go through all the details of the hospital, the team has dedicated volunteers on a daily basis to do this. Through the telephone inquiry investigation, to verify which hospitals can do obstetric examination, which hospitals can deliver, and there are spare delivery rooms.

Key details will also be asked, for example, whether hospitals treat pregnant women differently from those who are infected, or else pregnant women are at greater risk when they arrive at the hospital. As the situation changes from day to day, volunteers are constantly checking for updates.

During the exchange, the volunteers found that pregnant and lying-in women often expressed anxiety because they had many problems and were worried about where it was safer to go for a prenatal check-up and which hospital to go to for delivery, even having a car to go to the hospital.

How to get to the hospital after the traffic shutdown in Wuhan has really bothered many pregnant women. Through communication with the local care team, the dolphins and volunteers found four vehicles to provide emergency medical services when pregnant women need to give birth. So far, two infected pregnant women have been assisted to give birth in hospital, and another five women have gone to the hospital on their own, supported by information from the volunteers.

In practice, dolphins also face some problems that they don't know how to solve. For example, some pregnant women were diagnosed with a highly suspected infection but failed to get a nucleic acid test. If there is no new pneumonia, the mother to designated hospitals may be cross-infection; if there is, to the General Hospital will bring risks to health care workers. Volunteers can only report the situation to the government departments, let each other try to coordinate.

Dolphins believe that the current group of pregnant and lying-in women most need to solve the problem is the smooth flow of medical treatment. The government should designate a place where pregnant and lying-in women can have a pregnancy test and a pneumonia test on a priority basis. If confirmed, there should be a nearby hospital, the hospital should have delivery room, someone can deliver a baby, take care of the mother. At the same time, also want to do a good job of protection, do a good job screening to prevent cross-infection.

On January 28, the Wuhan Health Commission issued a document requiring designated hospitals to ensure medical care for special patients such as parturients. One by one, the volunteers found that only the Concorde Hospital said it could take them, but the hospital had no beds, was short of protective materials, and the renovation of the ward was progressing slowly.

Through their interactions with pregnant women, dolphins have discovered that the psychological support pregnant women need is more than just words of comfort and counseling. More important is to do something practical, such as providing timely information in the group, arranging for the doctor to do the question-and-answer. "Don't make them feel helpless. Knowing someone is helping them is relatively less stressful. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A Dolphin retweets a video of a mother and baby on friendagenda. Photo courtesy of the respondents

"A temporary separation for better love. "

In fact, this special group has also been the concern of the relevant departments.

On January 28, the medical rescue team of the new pneumonia prevention and Control Headquarters in Wuhan issued a document requiring relevant medical structures to ensure medical care for pregnant women and other special patients.

On the afternoon of February 1, the National Health Commission held a press conference. One of the main topics was to brief the media on the health protection of pregnant and lying-in Women, infants and child care institutions in the prevention and control of the new type of pneumonia.

Zhao Yangyu, director of obstetrics at the Third Hospital of Peking University, said at the press conference that the resistance of pregnant women who have been diagnosed with new-type pneumonia is relatively low, and they are prone to some sudden illnesses, the medical establishment will treat the pregnant woman's life in the first place.

The Hubei Provincial Women's Federation also pays attention to the group of pregnant and lying-in women. The Hubei Women's Federation and the all-china Women's Federation are concerned about this group and will do their best to provide them with some help, the relevant official of the Hubei Women's Federation said in an interview. Such as pregnant and lying-in women for pregnancy care, pregnancy check-up and other related knowledge of the Popular Science. At the same time, for some cases to the Women's Federation will also give help, try to coordinate with the relevant departments.

On Jan. 29, with the help of the community, Liu was finally admitted to a general hospital. After two hours of Caesarean section, her daughter was born and she became the only one in her family who was not infected.

On January 31, with the help of a team of volunteer dolphins, Gong was admitted to a designated hospital for special patients with a new type of pneumonia. The next night at 7:00, a 7.1-pound baby boy was born under the much-anticipated gaze. How many years later, I wonder if he will know, in order to come to this world, parents have gone through many difficulties, and how many people have worked together.

On Feb. 1, the dolphins retweeted a video of a mother and her baby on facebook. In the picture, a baby lies next to its mother with its eyes closed, crying loudly. The mother, who has been diagnosed with new-type pneumonia, will be transferred to a neonatal hospital after giving birth, while the adults will remain hospitalized, the Dolphin said. Retweeted, the dolphins in the circle of friends said, "temporary separation, is for better love. "

On the afternoon of February 2, the new pneumonia prevention and Control Headquarters in Wuhan issued circular No. 10: On the basis of earlier fixed-point quarantine and home quarantine, close contacts of fever patients and new-type pneumonia patients who have been diagnosed as having pneumonia symptoms in fever outpatient clinics throughout the city will be transported by vehicle from each district to a centralized isolation observation point, for Medical Observation, treatment or other preventive measures. During the period of isolation, accommodation, medical observation and treatment were provided free of charge in all districts. Other fever patients from the community continue to implement home isolation and observation measures.

In the view of observers, this measure will be effective in easing the fever of pregnant women in transportation, family isolation and medical difficulties.

(all interviewees in this article are pseudonyms)
